  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.5.1">
<l>pārāya tuṇṭumiḻnta pavaḷat tūṇaip paṭukaṭali lamutattaip parivāy kīṇṭa</l>
<l>cīrāṉai yemmāṉait toṇṭar taṅkaḷ cintaiyuḷḷē muḷaitteḻunta tīṅka rumpiṉai</l>
<l>pōrāṉaik kompocitta pōrēṟ ṟiṉaip puṇarmaruta miṟanaṭanta poṟkuṉ ṟiṉai</l>
<l>kārāṉai yiṭarkkaṭinta kaṟpa kattaik kaṇṭatunāṉ kaṭalmallait talaca yaṉattē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>My beholding of the coral column who ate and disgorged</l>
<l rend="indent">that which is an expanse, the nectar in the crashing sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">the elegant one who split the horse’s mouth,</l>
<l>Our lord, the sweet sugarcane which arises,</l>
<l rend="indent">sprouting in the minds of his devotees,</l>
<l>The battle bull who broke the battle elephant’s tusk, the gold mountain</l>
<l rend="indent">who walked [between] the twined marutu-s so they broke,</l>
<l>The kalpaka tree which ended the suffering of the black elephant</l>
<l rend="indent">was in Talacayaṉam at Mallai by the sea.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
